HEADWORD: Castigation
<hw>Cas`ti*ga"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>catigatio</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Corrective punishment; chastisement; reproof;
pungent criticism.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The keenest <qex>castigation</qex> of her slanderers.</q>
<rj><qau>W. Irving.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Emendation; correction.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Castigator</ent>⟦br⟧
